Data Streams in Data Cloud

Data streams are the connections and associated data ingested into Data Cloud.

Navigate, edit, and review data stream schedules in this help section. Review the Data Sources in Data Cloud section to know about data streams supported in Data Cloud and the steps to create the data streams.

Acceleration in Data Federation
When acceleration is enabled while creating a data stream, data is retrieved periodically from the partner. The data is persisted in the Accelerated data lake objects in Data Cloud.
Data Streams Tab Navigation
On the Data Cloud Data Streams tab, you can view all previously created data streams, the data streams you own, or all the data streams. You can also create a data stream.
Data Stream Schedule in Data Cloud
Data streams can operate on different refresh schedules. Learn more about how and when these data streams update.
Data Stream Settings
You can edit the settings of data streams that use Amazon S3, Google Cloud Storage (GCS), and SFTP connectors.
Data Lake Object Naming Standards
Use these naming guidelines for data lake objects.
Record Modified Field
The record modified field is set when defining the source object during setup in Data Cloud.
Create a Data Stream from a Data Kit
When you create a data stream from a data kit in your target org, the data model objects are available automatically. When adding a data model to a data kit, a custom data model is added as is. If you’re adding a standard data model, only the custom mappings and custom fields are packaged.
Create an Unstructured Data Lake Object from a Data Kit
After you have deployed your data kit in Data Cloud, you can create an unstructured data lake object (UDLO). All fields are automatically mapped.
Disable a Data Stream Field
If a field is no longer required in a data stream, you can disable it in Data Cloud. Disabling a field removes it from the data stream, and no new data is ingested. After you disable a field you can’t enable it again, but existing data remains in Data Cloud. You can’t assign the name of a disabled field to a new field.
Delete a Data Stream
You can delete a data stream in Data Cloud if the connection is no longer needed.
Edit a Data Stream
You can edit a data stream in Data Cloud for the Amazon S3, GCS, Azure, Marketing Cloud Engagement, and SFTP connectors. Changing the name of a data stream doesn’t change the name of the DLO that the data stream uses.
Delete Ingested Records in Data Cloud
You can delete data ingested into Data Cloud. Your data stream must have an upsert refresh mode. The deletion process depends on the type of connector that you’re using.
Supported File Formats in Data Cloud
Data Cloud supports various files and compression formats for your data stream sources.
Refresh History of Data Streams and Data Lake Objects
Data Cloud provides record-level statistics of the data ingested by data streams and records processed into a data lake object (DLO).
Using an Existing Data Lake Object to Create a Data Stream
You can use an existing data lake object (DLO) when creating an S3, Google Cloud Storage, or SFTP data stream. The data stream that initially created the DLO defines the characteristics, such as the primary key, event date time, and record modified field. You can convey how the new data stream’s fields conform to the existing DLO fields.
